1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,360
I just wanted to survive one night without being humiliated again.

2
00:00:03,780 --> 00:00:05,000
My ex would be at the party.

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:08,500
The  entire  elite  would  be  watching,  and  I  couldn't  bear

4
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:10,220
to  show  up  alone  as  the  woman  abandoned

5
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:10,960
at the altar.

6
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:14,580
So  I  hired  an  escort,  charming,  elegant,

7
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:15,600
and  mysterious.

8
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:19,420
He  seemed  far  too  dangerous  for  someone  paid  to  smile,  but

9
00:00:19,420 --> 00:00:21,240
he  was  the  only  one  who  defended  me  when

10
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:22,840
they tried to destroy me in public.

11
00:00:23,340 --> 00:00:26,620
The  problem  is  that,  in  the  middle  of  the  party,  his

12
00:00:26,620 --> 00:00:28,240
face  appeared  on  every  TV,

13
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:31,520
wanted, dangerous, mafia boss.

14
00:00:32,020 --> 00:00:34,360
And now the man I hired to pretend to be my date,

15
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:36,520
might have been the biggest risk of my life.

16
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,900
The  confirmed  guest  list  hit  my  phone  at  9 .42  in  the  morning,

17
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,120
and  I  knew,

18
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:44,060
from the silence the device made before it buzzed,

19
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:46,140
that something was about to ruin my Saturday.

20
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:50,280
I  was  in  a  robe,  barefoot  in  the  apartment  kitchen,  balancing

21
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,020
a  black  coffee  in  my  right  hand,

22
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,720
and my work tablet in my left.

23
00:00:54,060 --> 00:00:56,500
The hotel's charity gala was happening that night,

24
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,760
and I'd spent the entire week pretending it was just another event.

25
00:01:00,260 --> 00:01:03,200
Pretending was the most constant exercise of my adult life.

26
00:01:03,460 --> 00:01:05,000
I'd perfected it after the altar.

27
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:06,440
I opened the file.

28
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:09,480
I scrolled my finger down the names in alphabetical order.

29
00:01:09,960 --> 00:01:13,200
The coffee went cold in my hand, before I reached the letter H.

30
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,980
Calvin-Harth, plus one.

31
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:20,260
I set the cup down slowly, with the delicacy of someone diffusing a bomb,

32
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:24,600
and sat on the counter because my legs had decided this was a good moment to stop cooperating.

33
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:29,100
No, I said to myself out loud to the refrigerator, which had no opinion.

34
00:01:29,780 --> 00:01:30,880
No, no, no.

35
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,120
The plus one next to his name bothered me more than the name itself.

36
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,880
I knew who the plus one was.

37
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:37,420
The whole city knew.

38
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:42,760
Tisha Rome had posted three times the previous weekend, a video of herself trying on dresses,

39
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:45,740
saying, in the voice of someone chewing meringue,

40
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:50,280
that she was going to the gala of the year, with an old love turned new.

41
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:52,920
Old love turned new was the elegant way of saying,

42
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,760
a wily across his ex-fianse.

43
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,220
Eleguance never fooled anyone in Chicago.

44
00:01:57,980 --> 00:02:02,640
I stood up, sat down, stood up again, walked to the window and back.

45
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,840
The first crisis was about the dress.

46
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,600
I'd chosen a black one.

47
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:12,660
Long modest neckline, entire back exposed, because I wanted to be remembered as the woman who

48
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:16,220
organized the gala, not as the woman who showed up to be stared at.

49
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,100
Now the dress seemed like a joke.

50
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:19,140
Two modest.

51
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:20,400
Two sad.

52
00:02:20,940 --> 00:02:22,620
A dress for someone who'd given up.

53
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:25,180
The second crisis was about Calvin's parents.

54
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:26,460
They'd be there.

55
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,640
Their hotel was three blocks from mine.

56
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:32,600
They'd been signing checks to the charity foundation since before I was born.

57
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:35,800
And his father had the sinister habit of calling me dear.

58
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:38,900
As if the word still had a one-way ticket to our future.

59
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:45,080
The third crisis, the worst, came when I sat back down on the counter and realized that Chicago

60
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:49,300
had far too good a memory for a woman who'd been left at the altar and remained single.

61
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,760
The city didn't forget.

62
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,580
The sponsors didn't forget.

63
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,860
The society columnist didn't forget.

64
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:59,560
And I, no matter how many years I'd spent bearing that night under spreadsheets,

65
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:00,660
didn't forget either.

66
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:01,940
The doorbell rang.

67
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,460
I know you're in crisis.

68
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,200
Sir, I said before I could even open the door.

69
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:07,440
I know you.

70
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,560
I saw the list.

71
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:11,260
I brought decent coffee because yours is poison.

72
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:15,540
Sir, I Dom had been my best friend and catering partner for six years.

73
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,700
And she had the peculiarity of treating handsome men like poorly packaged

74
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:22,260
problems and emotional crises like recipes.

75
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:28,620
She walked in on low heels, hair pinned up on top of her head, two paper cups in her hand,

76
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,480
and a bag hanging from her shoulder that smelled like butter.

77
00:03:32,060 --> 00:03:32,820
Calvin confirmed.

78
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,740
I said, closing the door behind her.

79
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:36,780
I read it.

80
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:37,560
With Tisha.

81
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,340
I saw her video with the mustard colored dress.

82
00:03:40,340 --> 00:03:43,080
Sir, I set the cups on the counter and looked at me.

83
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,060
You look like you slept three hours.

84
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,600
I slept four.

85
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:47,440
Lire.

86
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,980
She nudged me onto a stool and set the cup in front of me.

87
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,140
I sniffed it.

88
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,480
It was coffee with cinnamon.

89
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:56,220
And something sweet I could never identify.

90
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:57,500
The ritual.

91
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:58,860
Higher an escort.

92
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,100
Sir, I said.

93
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:04,920
Without preamble, biting into a croissant that had appeared out of nowhere in her hand.

94
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:05,780
I choked.

95
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:06,620
What?

96
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,000
You heard me?

97
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:08,740
Sir, I.

98
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:09,640
Noelia.

99
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:12,880
I'm not going to hire a man to pretend he's in love with me.

100
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:14,860
You don't need him to pretend he's in love.

101
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:16,780
You just need him to pretend he's present.

102
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:17,880
She chued.

103
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,580
The difference is the budget.

104
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:20,420
No.

105
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,780
Think about it.

106
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:22,260
No.

107
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:24,540
You're going to walk into that hall alone.

108
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:27,640
With Calvin and his influencer laughing at the front table.

109
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:31,820
And the sponsors looking at you like they're watching a documentary about a wounded animal.

110
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:33,380
Is that what you want?

111
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,200
Sir, I.

112
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:34,860
No.

113
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,080
Fourth time.

114
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:36,800
You'll cave.

115
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:38,200
I looked at her.

116
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,700
She looked back at me.

117
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:40,260
Calm.

118
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,140
Chewing.

119
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:44,840
With the patience of someone who'd already won the argument before it started.

120
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,160
I sighed.

121
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,240
I took a long sip of the cinnamon coffee.

122
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:49,680
I looked at the ceiling.

123
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,180
I looked at the tablet.

124
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,400
I looked at the name Calvin Harth plus one on the screen.

125
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:56,900
And felt that old tightness in my chest.

126
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:01,700
The tightness that always came when I thought about having to smile for photographers while he

127
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,320
walked by.

128
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:04,740
How do you even hire an escort on a Saturday?

129
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,200
Surized smiled.

130
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:09,100
The kind of smile I should have learned to distrust.

131
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:11,540
She pulled her phone from her back pocket.

132
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,140
Pushed it toward me.

133
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,480
App, discreet.

134
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,720
Elite only.

135
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:16,760
Triple verification.

136
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,240
Contractual confidentiality.

137
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,600
It's already open on the registration page.

138
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:22,760
You're terrifying.

139
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,080
I'm efficient.

140
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:25,400
There's a difference.

141
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:26,780
I took the phone.

142
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:29,560
The screen showed a dark, sober interface.

143
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:31,940
No photos of shirtless men.

144
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,220
No clingy promises.

145
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:35,380
Just registration fields.

146
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,360
A suggested hourly rate.

147
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:41,560
And a clause in small letters saying the escort offered no service beyond social

148
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,540
companionship.

149
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:43,820
I read it twice.

150
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,360
I breathed.

151
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,700
I filled in the field sitting on the kitchen counter.

152
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:51,260
While Surai watched me with the attention of someone observing surgery.

153
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,200
Name.

154
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:53,700
Noelia Cross.

155
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:54,560
Event.

156
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:55,820
Charity gala.

157
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:56,680
Hotel.

158
00:05:57,180 --> 00:05:58,240
Black tie attire.

159
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,040
Duration.

160
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:00,380
Five hours.

161
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:01,320
Notes.

162
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,940
Needs to know how to behave among sponsors.

163
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:06,160
Needs to not ask questions.

164
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:10,000
Needs to be handsome enough to shut the mouth of a man named Calvin Harth.

165
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,800
I deleted the last line.

166
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,120
Re-wrote it.

167
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,340
Absolute discretion.

168
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,120
Impeccable presentation.

169
00:06:16,980 --> 00:06:17,760
I tapped confirm.

170
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:20,200
The app charged my card without ceremony.

171
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,200
A confirmation message appeared saying a compatible profile would be assigned within two hours,

172
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:28,900
and that the escort would arrive at the provided address at 7 o'clock sharp.

173
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:29,700
Done.

174
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:30,700
I said.

175
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,080
And my stomach dropped a whole inch in word.

176
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:33,880
Done.

177
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,680
Surai repeated satisfied.

178
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:38,360
I just made the dumbest decision of my life.

179
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:40,960
You've been making dumb decisions since I met you.

180
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:41,820
It's a constant.

181
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,400
I only support the ones with address involved.

182
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:46,240
I laughed despite myself.

183
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,100
The laugh came out half horse.

184
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:49,400
Half relieved.

185
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,740
Half terrified.

186
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:54,760
Surai pushed me toward the bathroom with the rest of the croissant in her hand.

187
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,280
And the order to shower while there was still time.

188
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,700
I arrived at the hotel at five in the afternoon.

189
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:02,140
I came in through the back service door.

190
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:07,300
As always, because I like to see the operation from the inside before heading up to the hall.

191
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,820
The main lobby was already being set up.

192
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:12,980
Tall arrangements of white hydrangeas, gold ropes,

193
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:16,640
the red carpet I'd argued about with the general manager for three weeks.

194
00:07:17,140 --> 00:07:20,240
I crossed the interior hallway to the event room on the second floor,

195
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:25,040
and the smell of wax and citrus perfume reminded me that this was my ground.

196
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:30,300
Regardless of Calvin, of Tisha, of hired men or messages from my mother,

197
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:32,260
asking if I decided to cut my hair.

198
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,720
The team was in formation, florist checking volume,

199
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:39,960
Maytree reviewing the dinner sequence, sound engineer testing a microphone.

200
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:45,740
I passed by each one, repeating the day's orders, adjusting a tablecloth here,

201
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:49,460
moving a stand there, pretending with reasonable success,

202
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:52,240
that my heart wasn't beating an extra count per second.

203
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:56,020
It was when I came up the side hallway of the lobby that I saw him.

204
00:07:56,380 --> 00:08:00,600
Calvin was standing near the reception desk, chatting with the evening receptionist,

205
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,040
with the rehearsed smile of someone who knows he's being watched.

206
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:08,580
Hair combed to the side, navy suit, champagne colored tie.

207
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:10,880
He saw me before I could turn toward the stairs.

208
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:14,660
Noelia, he said my name the same way he always did,

209
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,080
drawing out the final vowel, as if the name were still a caress.

210
00:08:18,580 --> 00:08:20,200
Calvin, what a coincidence.

211
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:21,840
You're at the event.

212
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,060
It's not a coincidence.

213
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:27,460
It's a list. He smiled, walked three steps toward me,

214
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:31,100
slow, with that calm of a man who loves having an audience,

215
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:34,700
and stopped five feet from me. He smelled like the same bitter

216
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,100
collone from two years ago.

217
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:39,460
The smell gave me a small wave of nausea in the pit of my stomach.

218
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:44,540
You look beautiful. He said, low, you always look beautiful when you're nervous.

219
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:48,780
I'm not nervous. You are. You bite the inside of your cheek.

220
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:52,380
You still do that. I stopped biting the inside of my cheek.

221
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:54,220
I hated that he was right.

222
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,300
Calvin, I have an event to run.

223
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:59,020
I know. You always had events to run.

224
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:03,960
He leaned in slightly, just the shoulder, just enough that no one could hear but me.

225
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:05,600
Tisha's excited to meet you.

226
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,220
I told her you'd understand.

227
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:08,780
You always understood.

228
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:12,420
The blood went cold somewhere between my collar bones and my chin.

229
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,040
I smiled. It was a trained smile.

230
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:19,600
Professional. The kind I reserved for difficult clients and curious journalists.

231
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,920
How sweet. I said.

232
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:26,960
And my voice came out firm, which I silently thanked some goddess of sarcasm for.

233
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,980
Tell her I reserved your seats near the band.

234
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:31,520
Great acoustics. You'll hear everything.

235
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:32,900
Calvin blinked.

236
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:36,140
For a second, just one. His smile wavered.

237
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:38,340
You recovered before I could savor it.

238
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:40,820
You haven't changed a bit. Neither of you.

239
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:43,520
I turned my back before he could find his next line.

240
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,860
I climbed the side stairs with the calm of someone who isn't fleeing.

241
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:52,260
On the first landing, I pressed my hand against the wall and waited for the blood to return to my

242
00:09:52,260 --> 00:09:55,480
fingers. The wall was cold. So were my fingers.

243
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:58,600
The phone buzzed in my pocket. I took it out.

244
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:03,100
I looked. The message from the app glowed on the screen with a short, neutral notice.

245
00:10:03,660 --> 00:10:07,820
Your escort for the evening will arrive at the hotel's main entrance in 15 minutes.

246
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,700
Confidentiality confirmed.

247
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:14,360
Enjoy the event. I breathed. I looked at the hallway clock.

248
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:19,420
There were exactly 15 minutes until a stranger would come through the hotels revolving door

249
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:23,360
and take the place I'd bought. For some reason, in that instant,

250
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:28,060
with my hand still pressed against the cold wall and my heart still out of rhythm because of

251
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:32,080
Calvin. I had the very clear sensation that I was about to make a mistake.

252
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:37,420
In a way I hadn't yet learned to name. The hotel's backstage had a smell of its own.

253
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:43,340
Wax, reheated coffee, perfume from the flower shop, the faint tang of the tile the cleaning

254
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:47,220
crew scrubbed before every big event. I got there five minutes early,

255
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:51,760
pretending to check the positioning of the waiters. When really I was just looking for something

